            <h2>——Quantitative Analysis of Children’s Sedentary Behaviors</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
            <h3>Preview</h3>
            <p>In order to explore the relationship between different sitting positions and pressure data, we conduct field research in a primary school, and carry out experiments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
            <h3>Experiment Design</h3>
            <p>
                    <b>Purpose</b></br>
                    We detect the pressure when children is doing writing, painting and reading in order to obtain pressure data under the natural state, take videos and use the coordinate to record the bending degree so as to analyze the pressure value in oblique and bending situations.</br>
                    <b>Assumption</b></br>
                    · The sitting position and body pressure are quite different when children perform different tasks </br>
                    · We can speculate the sitting position of children through the pressure data sampling of a cushion plane</br>
                    <b>Tasks</b></br>
                    Taking records of:</br>
                    · Bacis physical information of children</br>
                    · Changes in sitting posture when children perform different tasks </br>
                    · Real-time data obtained by pressure mats    
                    <table class="table-4" width="100%">
